      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Solver passes standard NAFEMS benchmark suite for linear static and contact problems; patch-test compliance confirmed.",
      "rationale": "Ansys Mechanical and the FDA in-house solver have both been verified against NAFEMS linear static benchmarks and Hertzian contact reference solutions. Code verification is adequate for the structural fidelity required by the COU."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Mesh convergence study demonstrates QoI change < 2% between successive refinements; GCI < 5%.",
      "rationale": "A three-level mesh refinement study was performed on the pedicle screw shank and rod junction. Stiffness QoI varied by 1.4% between the medium and fine meshes; GCI estimated at 3.1%. The production mesh uses the medium-density configuration, which is within the convergence plateau."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Residual norms converge to < 1e-6 for all load steps; no negative pivot warnings.",
      "rationale": "All quasi-static load steps converged with force residuals below 1e-7. No convergence failures or negative pivot warnings were recorded across the 11-specimen ensemble. Achieved level exceeds required level."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Independent model review by second analyst; checklist-based QA sign-off documented.",
      "rationale": "Each modeling team conducted an independent peer review of boundary conditions, material assignments, and contact definitions prior to submission. A standardised V&V checklist was signed off by a reviewer not involved in model construction."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Continuum elasto-plastic constitutive model with isotropic hardening; contact formulation captures screw-rod interface slip; validated against independent coupon data.",
      "rationale": "The Ti-6Al-4V screw and CoCr rod are modelled with bilinear isotropic hardening calibrated from tensile coupon tests. Frictional contact (mu=0.2) is applied at the set-screw/rod interface. Model form is appropriate for the quasi-static compression-bending regime of ASTM F1717."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Material properties sourced from lot-specific tensile testing; geometric inputs from CMM measurements of test articles; torque preload from calibrated torque wrench records.",
      "rationale": "Elastic modulus, yield strength, and tangent modulus were measured from three tensile coupons cut from the same material lot as the test constructs. CMM measurements of screw outer diameter and rod diameter were used to populate the FEA geometry. Set-screw torque was recorded for each specimen and applied as a preload boundary condition. Uncertainty in material properties and torque is characterised probabilistically as part of the UQ activity; dominant input drivers will be ranked in a forthcoming sensitivity analysis that was not completed within the current assessment window."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "N >= 10 specimens from a single production lot; dimensional inspection confirms conformance to design drawing.",
      "rationale": "Eleven non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw constructs were assembled from a single production lot. Dimensional inspection confirmed all screws and rods were within drawing tolerances. Sample size satisfies the pre-specified acceptance criterion."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Testing conducted under at least two distinct fixation torque levels or two rod diameters to bound the operating envelope.",
      "rationale": "Testing was performed at a single set-screw torque (4 Nm) and a single rod diameter (5.5 mm CoCr). Although this matches the intended COU, it does not span the full fixation torque range specified in the acceptance criterion. This factor is below the required level and is identified as a known gap in the assessment."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "FEA input parameters (geometry, material, boundary conditions) are demonstrably equivalent to the physical test article parameters within stated measurement uncertainties.",
      "rationale": "A parameter equivalency table maps each FEA input to its corresponding measured experimental value, with traceability to calibrated instruments. Geometric and material deviations between FEA and physical specimens are within the combined measurement uncertainty budget."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "E/uval < 1.96 for all three QoIs across all 11 specimens; mean relative error < 10%.",
      "rationale": "The validation metric E/uval was computed for stiffness, yield force, and force at 40 mm displacement. All values were below 1.96 (range 0.31–1.74). Mean relative errors were 4.2%, 6.8%, and 5.1% respectively. Both acceptance criteria are satisfied."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs (stiffness, yield force, force at 40 mm) are directly linked to the clinical failure modes identified in the risk analysis.",
      "rationale": "Construct stiffness relates to load-sharing with the vertebral column; yield force and force at 40 mm displacement are direct surrogates for implant fracture and permanent deformation failure modes documented in the device risk file. The selected QoIs are clinically relevant and traceable to the COU decision."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation scenario (ASTM F1717 static compression-bending) is the same loading mode and construct configuration as the COU.",
      "rationale": "The validation activity replicates the COU geometry, loading mode, and fixation configuration exactly. ASTM F1717 is the regulatory standard test for pedicle screw constructs, and the FEA model was exercised under identical boundary conditions to those applied in the physical test. Validation relevance is high."
    }
